## Proposed Changes

### Phase 1: AI Chatbot & Educational Tutor (The "Why")
Currently, the ChatbotActivity sends real requests to Gemini but doesn't persist conversations long-term, nor does it dynamically pull the specific context phrase correctly when launched from an error card.

- **[MODIFY] [ChatbotActivity.java](file:///c:/Users/asus/AndroidStudioProjects/GrammarHelper/app/src/main/java/com/example/grammarhelper/ui/ChatbotActivity.java)**
  - Implement full SQLite saving/loading using `ChatHistoryDAO`.
  - Ensure the "Smart Quick Chips" (Explain, Rewrite, Quiz) automatically capture the `currentContextText`.
  - Add logic to handle the `Intent` extra properly when the "Why?" button is clicked in the [ErrorReviewActivity](file:///c:/Users/asus/AndroidStudioProjects/GrammarHelper/app/src/main/java/com/example/grammarhelper/ui/ErrorReviewActivity.java#18-95) or Editor.

### Phase 2: Complete the Error Review Panel
Currently, the Error Review Panel displays hardcoded "Mock Data" (like "The dog bark").

- **[MODIFY] [ErrorReviewActivity.java](file:///c:/Users/asus/AndroidStudioProjects/GrammarHelper/app/src/main/java/com/example/grammarhelper/ui/ErrorReviewActivity.java)**
  - Remove all mock data.
  - Implement logic to receive the `List<GrammarError>` via an `Intent` (Serializable/Parcelable) or a shared `ViewModel` directly from [SmartEditorActivity](file:///c:/Users/asus/AndroidStudioProjects/GrammarHelper/app/src/main/java/com/example/grammarhelper/ui/SmartEditorActivity.java#35-204).
  - Fix the "Fix All" button so it actually applies the corrections to the text in the Smart Editor.

### Phase 3: Dashboard Analytics & Data Pipeline
The Progress Dashboard UI (with MPAndroidCharts) is built, but it relies on placeholder logic.

- **[MODIFY] [DashboardActivity.java](file:///c:/Users/asus/AndroidStudioProjects/GrammarHelper/app/src/main/java/com/example/grammarhelper/ui/DashboardActivity.java)**
  - Connect the [PieChart](file:///c:/Users/asus/AndroidStudioProjects/GrammarHelper/app/src/main/java/com/example/grammarhelper/ui/DashboardActivity.java#82-115) to `errorLogDAO.getErrorDistribution()`.
  - Connect the [LineChart](file:///c:/Users/asus/AndroidStudioProjects/GrammarHelper/app/src/main/java/com/example/grammarhelper/ui/DashboardActivity.java#59-81) to actual `SessionDAO` historical grammar scores.
  - Replace the static String builder in [loadTopMistakes()](file:///c:/Users/asus/AndroidStudioProjects/GrammarHelper/app/src/main/java/com/example/grammarhelper/ui/DashboardActivity.java#116-133) with a dynamic RecyclerView or properly constrained ListView.
  - Compute actual "Streaks" by analyzing timestamps in `SessionDAO`.

### Phase 4: System Data Persistence & Settings
We need to ensure all sessions and errors are saved accurately so the Dashboard has data to read.

- **[MODIFY] [SmartEditorActivity.java](file:///c:/Users/asus/AndroidStudioProjects/GrammarHelper/app/src/main/java/com/example/grammarhelper/ui/SmartEditorActivity.java)**
  - Update [updateUIWithResult](file:///c:/Users/asus/AndroidStudioProjects/GrammarHelper/app/src/main/java/com/example/grammarhelper/ui/SmartEditorActivity.java#180-203) to batch-save all detected [GrammarError](file:///c:/Users/asus/AndroidStudioProjects/GrammarHelper/app/src/main/java/com/example/grammarhelper/model/GrammarError.java#3-29) objects into `ErrorLogDAO` as soon as analysis is complete.
  - Save the final `Session` object (with calculated grammar/clarity scores) into `SessionDAO` when the activity is destroyed or text is cleared.
- **[MODIFY] [SettingsActivity.java](file:///c:/Users/asus/AndroidStudioProjects/GrammarHelper/app/src/main/java/com/example/grammarhelper/ui/SettingsActivity.java)** (and [Config.java](file:///c:/Users/asus/AndroidStudioProjects/GrammarHelper/app/src/main/java/com/example/grammarhelper/util/Config.java))
  - Hook up the `SwitchMaterial` components to `SharedPreferences` so the "Daily Grammar Tip" and App Theme toggles actually apply system-wide settings.

